---
title: Grilled Lemon Pepper Steak with a Poblano Potato Jumble
description: Had enough of summertime grilling? Good, neither have we. We’re so obsessed with the grate-est way to cook that we’ve dedicated this whole recipe to the thrill of the grill. First the potatoes are wrapped in foil and roasted over the flames. Then on go the veggies, which are allowed to get a little charred and smoky. And the steak? You guessed it—sizzled until it gets those coveted sear marks. P.S.: This recipe can be adapted for the oven, just in case.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/grilled-lemon-pepper-steak-aee428c3.jpg
